def has_dirty_area(floor:item):
    # Function to check if there is any dirty area on the floor
    symbol has_dirt=exists area: item : dirty(area) and inside(area, floor)
    return has_dirt

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind floor: item where:
            is_floor(floor)
        # Select the floor to identify dirty areas

        if has_dirty_area(floor):
            # If we already know there are dirty areas on the floor, no need to search further
            foreach area: item:
                if dirty(area) and inside(area, floor):
                    achieve close_char(char, area) # Approach the dirty area
        else:
            # If no dirty areas are known, check each unvisited section of the floor
            foreach section: item:
                if inside(section, floor) and not visited(section):
                    observe(section, "Check is there any debris or dirt on the floor")
